OSMC (Open Source Media Center) has added support for the Raspberry Pi 3 Model B+. “After updating to OSMC’s March release, you can simply swap an SD card out from a Pi 2 or Pi 3 and put it in a Pi 3 B+,” it said. “The power requirements of the unit are increased, so we recommend using a good-quality power supply.” The latest OSMC update also includes several bug fixes and new support features, which includes: